{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17491570","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17491570"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T05:53:10+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T05:53:10+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"986"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"986","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/986"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.26,0.2,0.09,0.4,0.05]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"986"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"43673"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"986","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/986"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"986"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"28681"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"4"},{"type":"tags","id":"31"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"390"},{"type":"tags","id":"1087"},{"type":"tags","id":"1094"},{"type":"tags","id":"1144"},{"type":"tags","id":"1181"},{"type":"tags","id":"4962"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"8088"},{"type":"tags","id":"8224"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"5703"},{"type":"contributions","id":"6369"},{"type":"contributions","id":"14304"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42189"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44763"},{"type":"contributions","id":"45060"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"43673","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/43673"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 60-year-old woman presents with a six-week history of a rapidly enlarging, painless swelling in her neck. During this time she has also noticed that her voice has become hoarse, difficulty swallowing, and a brassy cough. She has a 20 pack-year smoking history. She has no other significant medical history and takes no regular medications.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, her pulse rate is 82/min, blood pressure 124/80 mmHg, respiratory rate 18/min, temperature 36.7\u00b0C, and SpO2 98% on room air. A large, uniform, non-tender mass is visible centrally over her neck (Image). There is no tremor present with outstretched hands. Her eyes area regular in external appearance. Reflexes are uniform bilaterally.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Papillary carcinoma of the thyroid","Multi-nodular goitre","Haemorrhage into a thyroid cyst","Anaplastic carcinoma of the thyroid","Hashimotos thyroiditis"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAnaplastic carcinoma of the thyroid \u003C/strong\u003Eis typically associated with a rapidly growing neck mass in addition to involvement of deeper neck structures. It typically affects older patients (over 65 years) but it can present in younger patients on occasion. Involvement of the deeper neck structures such as the recurrent laryngeal nerve and the oesophagus as indicated here by the hoarse voice and recent onset of dysphagia are characteristic as is early metastatic spread most commonly to the lungs. Note that anaplastic carcinomas are uncommon, comprising 1-2 % of thyroid cancers. Lymphoma of the thyroid would be a differential to consider in this case due to the possibility of rapid growth but involvement of underlying structures is less likely.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAlthough \u003Cstrong\u003Epapillary carcinoma of the thyroid \u003C/strong\u003Eis the most common subtype of thyroid carcinoma (followed by follicular carcinoma), it is not associated with the rapid growth described here nor the involvement of underlying neck structures.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMulti-nodular goitre \u003C/strong\u003Ewould also be a consideration for an undifferentiated neck mass, however they are typically associated with slow growth, symptoms of thyroid dysfunction and a multi-nodular mass on exam rather than the uniform lump described here. A simple goitre would not impinge on underlying structures.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHaemorrhage into a thyroid cyst \u003C/strong\u003Eis an extremely rare and associated with rapid symptom onset, taking hours or days rather than weeks, but is painful and usually manifests with deranged vital signs.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHashimotos thyroiditis \u003C/strong\u003Ewould not usually cause a rapidly growing mass and would be even less likely to impinge on underlying neck structures such as those presented here. There are also no symptoms of thyroid deficiency (e.g. weight gain and fatigue) that could indicate thyroiditis.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Anaplastic carcinoma of the thyroid gland is a poorly differentiated cancer of thyrocytes that characteristically involves impingement of underlying neck structures such as the recurrent laryngeal nerve to cause hoarseness and dysphagia."],"references":["Zamora EA, Khare S, Cassaro S. Thyroid Nodule. In: StatPearls [Online]. 2021. Available at: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK535422/","Chintakuntlawar A, Foote R, Kasperbauer J, Bible K. Diagnosis and Management of Anaplastic Thyroid Cancer. Endocrinology and Metabolism Clinics of North America. 2019;48(1):269-284. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/30717908/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"28681"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"986"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"15857"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"15857","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/15857"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/d438a520-ccad-40eb-a3de-9e486cff235a.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/d438a520-ccad-40eb-a3de-9e486cff235a.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":384,"height":440}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"28681","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/28681"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-03-25T14:18:09+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-08-15T22:37:32+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"986"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"43673"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"4","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf6c","name":"Endocrinology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"31","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/31"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf97","name":"Oncology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:45+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"64","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/64"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Diagnosis","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"72","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/72"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Graduating","synonyms":null,"description":"Only suitable for a graduating